<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-597-681  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 597 681.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  Nov 12 1990 n295 p82(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM ready to back the Mac; Big Blue to include Macintosh in OfficeVision.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Moran, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM plans to include Apple Macintosh in its OfficeVision officeautomation platform.andP;  The inclusion will probably first entail theMacintosh going into an IBM environment as a terminal, and at alater date becoming a full client.andP;  How long it will take isuncertain.andP;  The inclusion of Microsoft Windows 3.0 in IBM's suiteof products has already been approved for OfficeVision, but that,too, has an indefinite schedule.andP;  To date 500 applications havebeen announced for OfficeVision applications programminginterfaces (APIs).andP;  Analyst speculate that IBM will continue toexpand the number of APIs and implement a higher-level interfaceto accommodate non-IBM workstations.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Product development).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   OfficeVision (Office automation software) (Product enhancement)Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     Business PlanningEnhancementsOffice Automation SoftwareProduct DevelopmentConnectivity.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>